- After `rq = blk_get_request(...)` succeeds: multiple `return` paths do not release `rq` and/or `long_cmdp`
- Specifically:
  - `if ((dxfer_len <= 0) || (dxfer_dir == SG_DXFER_NONE)) return 0;` (leaks `rq`, and leaks `long_cmdp` when `cmd_len > BLK_MAX_CDB`)
  - `if (md) { ... res = sg_build_indirect(...); if (res) return res; }` (leaks `rq`, and may leak `long_cmdp`; may also leave partially-initialized scatter state)
  - `if (unlikely(iov_count > MAX_UIOVEC)) return -EINVAL;` (leaks `rq` and possibly `long_cmdp`)
  - `iov = memdup_user(...); if (IS_ERR(iov)) return PTR_ERR(iov);` (leaks `rq` and possibly `long_cmdp`)
  - Any error return after mapping attempts where `rq` has been obtained but not put

