IMPACT: A local unprivileged user who can issue SG_IO / sg requests can trigger these error/early-return paths repeatedly to leak kernel resources:
- **Kernel memory exhaustion** (leaked `long_cmdp`, indirect buffers, iovec copies in some paths if not freed elsewhere)
- **Request object exhaustion** (leaked `struct request`), potentially stalling I/O and causing **denial of service** system-wide
- Secondary effects: degraded performance, inability to allocate new requests, potential soft lockups/timeouts under load

FIX: Ensure all exit paths after acquiring resources release them, using a single cleanup block. Concretely:
1. Introduce `goto`-based error handling and always `blk_put_request(rq)` on failure/early return after `blk_get_request()` succeeds.
2. Free `long_cmdp` on all failure paths; define clear ownership:
   - If `rq->cmd` is set to `long_cmdp`, ensure it is freed when the request completes (e.g., in end_io handler) or revert `rq->cmd` to the embedded buffer and free `long_cmdp` before releasing the request on failure.
3. If `sg_build_indirect()` or reserve linking allocates/claims resources, add corresponding unwind calls on failure.

Example pattern (illustrative):

```c
int ret = 0;
...
rq = blk_get_request(...);
if (IS_ERR(rq)) { kfree(long_cmdp); return PTR_ERR(rq); }

...
if ((dxfer_len <= 0) || (dxfer_dir == SG_DXFER_NONE)) {
    ret = 0;
    goto out_put_rq;   // also handle long_cmdp ownership
}

...
if (unlikely(iov_count > MAX_UIOVEC)) { ret = -EINVAL; goto out_put_rq; }

...
if (md && (ret = sg_build_indirect(...))) goto out_put_rq;

...
if (iov_count) {
    iov = memdup_user(...);
    if (IS_ERR(iov)) { ret = PTR_ERR(iov); goto out_put_rq; }
    ...
    kfree(iov);
} else {
    ret = blk_rq_map_user(...);
}

if (ret) goto out_unwind_map; // if needed

return 0;

out_unwind_map:
    // undo sg_build_indirect / reserve link if applicable
out_put_rq:
    // if rq->cmd == long_cmdp and request won't complete, free it here
    if (rq->cmd == long_cmdp) rq->cmd = rq->__cmd; // or appropriate field
    kfree(long_cmdp);
    blk_put_request(rq);
    return ret;
